core.conflict

Class AbstractConflictSource<T,E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • core.conflict.AbstractConflictCandidate<T,E>
      • core.conflict.AbstractConflictSource<T,E>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the conflict source entity (the same type of the entities that define the conflict scope for this conflict source entity).
    E - The type of entities that underly the conflict arising by this conflict source entity
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    IConflictCandidate<T,E>, IConflictSource<T,E>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    OwningClassAssociationConflictSource, OwningClassAttributeConflictSource, OwningClassDependencyConflictSource

    public abstract class AbstractConflictSource<T,E>
extends AbstractConflictCandidate<T,E>
implements IConflictSource<T,E>
    an AbstractConflictSource abstract class that is used to factor the common interface and state of all concrete conflict source classes.

    It must be specialized by all concrete conflict source classes.
    Author:
    Bachar Rima

      • AbstractConflictSource

        public AbstractConflictSource(AbstractConflictScope<T,E> conflictScope,
                              T entity)
        Creates a conflict source having entity as its underlying entity and conflictScope as its associated conflict scope. It also initializes its lists of pre/post-transformation elements as empty array lists.
        Parameters:
        conflictScope - a conflict scope to define the conflict scope of this conflict source
        entity - an entity to be used as this conflict source's underlying entity
